sit for one or two semesters as part of a formal exchange agreement between VMI and their nations  military academies  They participate in the academic program and may participate in athletics and other extra curricular activities  Following the completion of their program at VMI  cadets return to the academy in their home nation  Each year military exchange cadets from France  Germany  and Lithuania spend one or two semesters at VMI  Follow the link below to set up an account with the Office of International Programs where you can access information designed to help ease your transition  Four Year Cadets International four year cadets come from many different countries and go through the same rigorous academic  military and athletic program as cadets from the United States  If you are an incoming international  rat  we have information to help you adjust to U S  and VMI culture  Follow the link below to set up an account with the Office of International Programs where you can access information designed to help ease your transition  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 